Below is the procedure for the installation.

For the installation you need the following libraries:
    numpy scipy matplotlib gmsh pandas numba colorama pickle

    (optional) : The following libraries are optional but can be useful to reduce your resolution time. I recommend the use of pypardiso or petsc4py.
    pypardiso petsc4py mpi4py scikit-umfpack scikits-sparse
	Note that pypardiso does not work with ARM processors

It is necessary to add in the PYTHONPATH the modules folder:
	
	on macOs :
		export PYTHONPATH:"$PYTHONPATH: .../PythonEF/modules"
		(in the .zprofile)

	on linux :
		export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH: .../PythonEF/modules
        (in the .bash_aliases)
		
	on windows : 
		modify system variables -> environment variables -> user variables
		PYTHONPATH .../PythonEF/modules
        

Build gmsh like a big person (optional):

	first you have to install opencascade : sudo port install opencascade
	then install fltk : sudo port install fltk

	On Mac you have to build the gmsh project
	https://gitlab.onelab.info/gmsh/gmsh
	In the applications folder:

	git clone 
	cd gmsh
	mkdir build
	mkdir bin
	cd build
	cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/Applications/gmsh/bin -DENABLE_BUILD_DYNAMIC=1 . 
	make 
	make install

	then add the path to gmsh.py
	export PYTHONPATH=".../PythonEF/modules:/Applications/gmsh/bin/lib"